Beginning with Tommaseo (comm. to vv. 25-27) commentators
have suggested a source in Ovid (^Metam~. V.388-391) for the shaded
garden here, the Sicilian scene of Proserpina's rape (see ^Purg.~
XXVII.49-51), where the forests above the pools in the hills of Enna
keep them protected from Apollo's rays.
..TCHR:
300
..AUTH:
