Some readers have found the three paces that must not yet be
crossed allegories of the three 'steps' of confession, contrition, and
satisfaction that await Dante later when he must deal with Beatrice's
accusation in cantos XXX and XXXI.  Others think they are only
indicative of a short distance and have no deeper meaning.
