Dante's double question refers to the explanation of Statius
(^Purg.~ XXI.43-72) that the earthquake marking his liberation from the
memory of sin was not, as Dante had imagined, a natural meteorological
event, but a supernatural one.  Just so the running water of the stream
and the constant breeze, Matelda will explain, are not natural
phenomena but supernatural ones, heavenly artifices to harmonize the
physical attributes of this place with its spiritual essence.
