Matelda essentially repeats what Statius had said below
(see the note to ^Purg.~ XXVIII.85-87): God limits the natural
meteorology of the mountain to the ante-purgatory.  The first humans,
Adam and Eve, were placed in this spot free of any such disturbance;
but they themselves, in their disobedience, disturbed the laws of
eternal nature in the garden (vv. 94-96).
