..TEXT:
When they were inspired on their holy mountain, Parnassus
(that is, when they were most inspired by their muses), the classical
poets sang of the age of gold (e.g., Ovid in the beginning of the
^Metamorphoses~, Virgil in his fourth ^Eclogue~).  In doing so, they
perhaps had some intimation of this place, scene of the true 'golden
age,' where mankind was created in innocence and joy.
..TCHR:
